GET /user/repos <p>Retrieve all repositories for the authenticated user.</p> <p>Request</p> <pre><code>GET /user/repos  
Authorization: Bearer &lt;YOUR_GITHUB_TOKEN&gt;  
Accept: application/vnd.github+json  
</code></pre> <p>Query Parameters</p> <ul> <li><code>type</code> (string) – <code>all</code> | <code>owner</code> | <code>public</code> | <code>private</code></li> <li><code>sort</code> (string) – <code>created</code> | <code>updated</code> | <code>pushed</code> | <code>full_name</code></li> <li><code>per_page</code> (integer) – number of items per page (default 30)</li> <li><code>page</code> (integer) – page number for pagination</li> </ul> <p>Response Example</p> <pre><code>[
    {
        "id": 1296269,
        "name": "Hello-World",
        "full_name": "octocat/Hello-World",
        "private": false,
        "html_url": "https://github.com/octocat/Hello-World",
        "owner": {
        "login": "octocat",
        "id": 1
        }
    }
]
</code></pre>

GET /repos/{owner}/{repo} <p>Retrieve notermation about a specific repository.</p> <p>Request</p> <pre><code>GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}  
Authorization: Bearer &lt;YOUR_GITHUB_TOKEN&gt;  
Accept: application/vnd.github+json  
</code></pre> <p>Path Parameters</p> <ul> <li><code>owner</code> – repository owner username</li> <li><code>repo</code> – repository name</li> </ul> <p>Query Parameters</p> <p>None.</p> <p>Response Example</p> <pre><code>{
"id": 1296269,
"name": "Hello-World",
"full_name": "octocat/Hello-World",
"private": false,
"html_url": "https://github.com/octocat/Hello-World",
"description": "This is your first repo!"
}
</code></pre>
